<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>Entertainment Guild Store is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy outlines how we handle your data when you use our web application.</p>

<h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Your name, email address, and password when you register an account</li>
    <li>Your order history and cart items</li>
    <li>Session data for login tracking</li>
</ul>

<h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
<ul>
    <li>To process your orders and display them in your history</li>
    <li>To authenticate and authorize user access based on role (Customer, Employee, Admin)</li>
</ul>

<h4>3. Data Storage and Protection</h4>
<p>Your data is stored securely in our SQL database and is only accessible to authorized users via role-based access. Passwords are stored in plain form for prototype purposes only.</p>

<h4>4. Data Sharing</h4>
<p>We do not share your data with any third parties.</p>

<h4>5. User Rights</h4>
<p>If you wish to modify or delete your account, please contact the site administrator.</p>

<p>For any questions regarding this policy, contact us at <strong>support@entertainmentguildstore.com</strong>.</p>
<h4>6. Educational Use Disclaimer</h4>
<p>
    This website is a student project developed for academic purposes only, as part of the INFT 3050 Web Programming course.
    All product images, names, and related content are used solely for demonstration and learning.
    No actual transactions will occur, and no personal data is collected or stored for commercial use.
</p>
